      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOLD TAG (2) is in hot form after clocking a flying 25.25 victory two back then followed up with a 25.33 win at Shepparton over 450m last time. Recent figures good for this and can measure up again. STITCH AND SHOUT (1) settled back off the inside but went through his gears strongly to find the frame with a 5.5 lengths third (30.52) at this track in Grade 5. Goes very well from this box. Has a strong record out of this box with four wins and a minor placing from eight starts. Racing well and deserves a win. FILL MY POCKETS (7) drew an outside box and was game in defeat when only 2 lengths from the winner Radar O'reilly in third(30.29) at this track. Will give a great sight again. IAN ALBERT (3) is worth including after a top-three finish most recently.",
